### City of Live Oak

Live Oak, California, is an officially [incorporated](/Municipal_corporation) municipality situated within the boundaries of [Sutter County, California](/Sutter_County,_California), in the United States of America. It plays a role in the broader [Yuba City Metropolitan Statistical Area](/Yuba_City_Metropolitan_Statistical_Area), which itself is a component of the larger [Greater Sacramento CSA](/Sacramento_metropolitan_area). The city’s administrative footprint extends to include a small, historically recognized enclave known as Stafford. According to the definitive [2020 United States census](/2020_United_States_census), Live Oak was home to 9,106 residents. This figure represented a discernible increase from the 8,392 individuals counted during the [2010 census](/2010_United_States_census).

#### Location

The geographical coordinates that pinpoint Live Oak are 39°16′33″N 121°39′36″W, with a corresponding decimal degree notation of 39.27583°N and -121.66000°W. This places it squarely within the [United States](/United_States), specifically in the state of [California](/California). It is nestled within [Sutter County](/Sutter_County,_California). The city achieved its official incorporation on January 22, 1947, marking its formal establishment as a self-governing entity.

The city is accessible via [Live Oak Blvd](/U.S._Route_99) and Pennington Road, a route that also provides access to the Leo Cheney Correctional Center.

