#### 2020 Census

The [2020 United States census](/2020_United_States_census) detailed the population of Live Oak to be 9,106 individuals. The population density was calculated at 2,917.7 inhabitants per square mile (1,126.5/km²). The racial composition of the city was reported as follows: 37.0% [White](/White_Americans), 1.5% [African American](/African_Americans), 1.9% [Native American](/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States), 13.7% [Asian](/Asian_Americans), 0.5% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_Americans). An additional 30.3% identified with other races, and 15.1% identified with two or more races. Notably, individuals of [Hispanic or Latino](/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans) origin, regardless of race, constituted 49.5% of the total population.

Regarding living arrangements, the census indicated that 98.9% of the population resided in households. A mere 0.2% lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, while 0.9% were in institutionalized settings.

The city comprised 2,734 households. Of these, 47.7% included children under the age of 18. Married-couple households accounted for 52.9%, with an additional 6.6% being cohabiting couple households. Female householders with no partner present represented 25.0%, and male householders without a partner present made up 15.5%. Single-person households constituted 17.8% of the total, with 8.9% of these being individuals aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.29 people. In terms of family structures, there were 2,100 families (representing 76.8% of all households), with an average family size that isn't explicitly stated here but is implied by the household size.

The age distribution revealed that 28.3% of the population was under 18 years of age. Those aged 18 to 24 comprised 9.6%, individuals aged 25 to 44 were 26.2%, the 45 to 64 age group accounted for 22.4%, and 13.5% were 65 years or older. The median age in Live Oak was 33.8 years. The gender distribution showed 96.6 males for every 100 females.

There were 2,836 housing units in total, with an average density of 908.7 units per square mile (350.9 units/km²). Of these units, 96.4% were occupied, totaling 2,734 units. Homeownership was prevalent, with 63.1% of occupied units being owner-occupied, while 36.9% were occupied by renters.

As of 2023, the U.S. Census Bureau estimated that 26.4% of Live Oak's population was foreign-born. Language spoken at home indicated that 55.1% spoke only English. [Spanish](/Spanish_language) was spoken by 27.0%, other [Indo-European languages](/Indo-European_languages) by 14.8%, Asian or Pacific Islander languages by 2.1%, and other languages by 0.9%. Educational attainment showed that 71.7% of residents aged 25 and older had completed high school, and 13.3% held a bachelor's degree.

The median household income in 2023 was reported as $66,590, with a [per capita income](/Per_capita_income) of $25,986. Approximately 11.8% of families and 15.1% of the overall population lived below the poverty line.

#### 2010 Census

The [2010 United States census](/2010_United_States_census) documented Live Oak's population at 8,392. The population density was considerably higher at 4,491.3 inhabitants per square mile (1,734.1/km²). The racial makeup was as follows: 53.5% [White](/White_(U.S._Census)), 1.6% [African American](/African_American_(U.S._Census)), 1.5% [Native American](/Native_American_(U.S._Census)), 11.7% [Asian](/Asian_(U.S._Census)), 0.2% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)). Individuals identifying with other races constituted 25.9%, and those identifying with two or more races were 5.5%. [Hispanic](/Hispanic_(U.S._Census)) or [Latino](/Latino_(U.S._Census)) individuals, regardless of race, numbered 4,093, or 48.8% of the population.

The census reported that 95.0% of the population (7,972 people) lived in households, with 0.3% in non-institutionalized group quarters and 4.7% (398 people) in institutionalized settings.

Live Oak contained 2,331 households. Of these, 49.8% had children under 18. Married-couple households living together accounted for 60.1%. Female householders without a husband present were 12.7%, and male householders without a wife present were 6.3%. Unmarried opposite-sex partnerships represented 5.2%, and same-sex married couples or partnerships were 0.6%. Non-family households included 17.2% single-person households, with 8.0% of these being individuals aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.42. Families, defined as households with at least one person related to the householder by birth, marriage, or adoption, constituted 79.2% of all households (1,845 families), with an average family size of 3.88.

The population distribution showed 30.6% under 18, 9.7% aged 18 to 24, 28.1% aged 25 to 44, 20.9% aged 45 to 64, and 10.7% aged 65 or older. The median age was 31.7 years. For every 100 females, there were 89.9 males, and for every 100 females aged 18 and over, there were 87.1 males.

There were 2,498 housing units, with an average density of 1,336.9 units per square mile (516.2 units/km²). Owner-occupied units numbered 1,535 (65.9%), while 796 units (34.1%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.6%, and the rental vacancy rate was 8.2%. A significant majority, 63.2% of the population (5,306 people), lived in owner-occupied housing, while 31.8% (2,666 people) resided in rental units.

